{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Labs Terrain Mesh ROP"], "type": "title", "extent": [0, 26], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [138, 235], "text": [" The Terrain Segment SOP allows you to convert the plugged in heightfield into geometry. "]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [235, 391], "text": ["The Terrain Segment SOP allows you to convert the plugged in heightfield into geometry. The tool allows for adaptive meshing based on heightfield details."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [442, 560], "text": ["This allows you to override which layer is used for the height information. Generally this value is \"height\"."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Height Layer"], "role": "item", "extent": [424, 442], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [576, 676], "text": ["This allows you to control how many chunks have to be generated from the input heightfield."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Tile Count"], "role": "item", "extent": [560, 576], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [691, 782], "text": ["When this toggle is enabled, the tool will color code all separate chunks for you."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Visualize"], "role": "item", "extent": [676, 691], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 4, "level": 2, "text": ["Segmenting"], "extent": [403, 424], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [818, 1038], "text": ["This parameter controls the base density of your generated mesh. A value of 1.0 will generate an equal amount of quads as there are voxels in the heightfield. Lower this value prior to enabling adaptive density."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Base Density"], "role": "item", "extent": [800, 818], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1060, 1170], "text": ["Enabling this toggle will have the tool calculate adaptive quad density based on heightfield details."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Adaptive Density"], "role": "item", "extent": [1038, 1060], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1194, 1418], "text": ["This allows you to control how many levels of adaptive density the tool has to generate. Higher will produce more adaptive detail. Please note that increasing this value will exponentially increase the cooking time."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Num Density Levels"], "role": "item", "extent": [1170, 1194], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1443, 1561], "text": ["The density distribution controls smoothing iterations prior to dividing the heightfield into adaptive quads."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Density Disribution"], "role": "item", "extent": [1418, 1443], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1582, 1694], "text": ["This ramp allows you to control how the adaptive density gets distributed over the heightfield details."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Density Falloff"], "role": "item", "extent": [1561, 1582], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 4, "level": 2, "text": ["Meshing"], "extent": [782, 800], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1732, 1832], "text": ["Enabling this toggle will force the UVs for all chunks to be distributed from 0-1 in total."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["0-1 UV per segment"], "role": "item", "extent": [1708, 1732], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 4, "level": 2, "text": ["UVs"], "extent": [1694, 1708], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1870, 2044], "text": ["Enabling this toggle will create a closed extruded chunk rather than an open planar surface. This might be useful if you plan on using this geometry for simulations."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Extrude Base"], "role": "item", "extent": [1852, 1870], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2055, 2143], "text": ["This controls the depth of the extrusion produced by the \"Extrude Base\" toggle."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Depth"], "role": "item", "extent": [2044, 2055], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2160, 2218], "text": ["This controls the direction of the extruded base."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Base Normal"], "role": "item", "extent": [2143, 2160], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2236, 2365], "text": ["This controls if the extruded bottom needs to be flat for all chunks, or if it should keep the shape of the heightfield."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Flatten Base"], "role": "item", "extent": [2218, 2236], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 4, "level": 2, "text": ["Extrusion"], "extent": [1832, 1852], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2399, 2498], "text": ["Enabling this toggle will store all chunks in a single file as sub-objects inside the FBX."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Single File"], "role": "item", "extent": [2382, 2399], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2518, 2566], "text": ["This specifies the output file on disk."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Output File(s)"], "role": "item", "extent": [2498, 2518], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2594, 2665], "text": ["Controls if the exported FBX should be binary or ASCII format."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Export in ASCII Format"], "role": "item", "extent": [2566, 2594], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2686, 2784], "text": ["This allows you to override the used FBX SDK version for export. Default is usually best."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["FBX SDK Version"], "role": "item", "extent": [2665, 2686], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2796, 2903], "text": ["Pressing this button will export the heightfield to disk as geometry using the above settings."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Export"], "role": "item", "extent": [2784, 2796], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 4, "level": 2, "text": ["Output"], "extent": [2365, 2382], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Parameters", "role": "section", "extent": [391, 403], "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "id": "parameters"}], "summary": [" The Terrain Segment SOP allows you to convert the plugged in heightfield into geometry. "], "type": "root", "attrs": {"version": null, "tags": "sidefxlabs,  model", "namespace": "labs", "internal": "labs::terrain_segment", "context": "sop", "type": "node", "icon": "terrainsegmentrop"}, "title": ["Labs Terrain Mesh ROP"]}